Abstract = {Several aspects of the pollination biology of Justicia candicans were
   studied in a population located in central Sonora, Mexico. The species
   flowered from January to April during the studied year (2003). Its
   flowers secreted up to 4 mu L of nectar that had 41 \% sucrose. It is
   self-compatible and visited primarily by the resident hummingbird,
   Cynanthus latirostris, and occasionally by the common bee, Apis
   mellifera.},
